4. The method of claim 1, wherein the patient has been diagnosed as having Type 2 diabetes on the basis of one or more of the following findings:
(a) hyperglycemia in conjunction with a normal or elevated level of insulin;
(b) hyperglycemia in conjunction with evidence of pancreatic β cell maintenance;
(c) hyperglycemia in conjunction with a blunted blood glucose response to insulin; and
(d) hyperglycemia and a family history of Type 2 diabetes.

